:INFO
Aquaponics Troubleshooting Guide
Common problems in small aquaponics systems and their practical solutions.

:TASK
[ ] High ammonia: reduce feeding, check for dead fish, add more aeration
[ ] High nitrite: increase plant density, do a 20% water change, add beneficial bacteria
[ ] Low pH: add potassium hydroxide or calcium carbonate in small doses
[ ] High pH: add pH down or food-grade phosphoric acid carefully
[ ] Algae overgrowth: shade the fish tank, no light on water surface
[ ] Plants yellowing: check iron levels, add chelated iron supplement
[ ] Fish gasping at surface: emergency aeration, check ammonia and oxygen levels

:NOTE
Test water parameters twice weekly while learning the system. Once stable, weekly testing is sufficient. Keep a log so you can see trends before they become crises.
